From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 16:06:17 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mgr/tox: drop `git ls-files cephadm` assertions from flake8
 env

Same root cause as 2017-cephadm-tox-drop-git-lsfiles-checks.patch: the
flake8 env asserts the exact count of `docker.io` / `quay.io`
references in cephadm/*.py via `git ls-files`, which fails on the
release tarball (no .git, zero matches, assertion trips).  The
flake8 lint itself passes.

These checks are only meaningful in a dev git checkout; on a frozen
tarball both counts are fixed.

Signed-off-by: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
---
 src/pybind/mgr/tox.ini | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/pybind/mgr/tox.ini b/src/pybind/mgr/tox.ini
index c2deb6272..7cff726ff 100644
--- a/src/pybind/mgr/tox.ini
+++ b/src/pybind/mgr/tox.ini
@@ -161,8 +161,6 @@ modules =
 commands =
     flake8 --config=tox.ini {posargs} \
       {posargs:{[testenv:flake8]modules}}
-    bash -c 'test $(git ls-files cephadm | grep ".py$" | grep -v tests | xargs grep "docker.io" | wc -l) == 3'
-    bash -c 'test $(git ls-files cephadm | grep ".py$" | grep -v tests | xargs grep "quay.io" | wc -l) == 8'

 [testenv:jinjalint]
 deps =
